Brandon Richards reports: California resident Sean Mortazi filed a class action lawsuit against TikTok Inc. on June 11, 2026, alleging a data breach exposed the personal data of more than 2.4 billion users worldwide. The complaint, filed in the U.S. District Court for the Central District of California, claims TikTok stored unencrypted data and skipped basic...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F07%2F11%2Ftiktok-class-action-alleges-data-breach-affected-2-4b-users%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dtiktok-class-action-alleges-data-breach-affected-2-4b-users&amp;action_name=TikTok%20class%20action%20alleges%20data%20breach%20affected%202.4B%20users&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
