A statement on ZEGO Textilveredelungszentrum GmbH&#8217;s website explains why they are filing for insolvency: Insolvency proceedings have been initiated – and why we are still looking ahead Ladies and gentlemen,  dear business partners, Today we are contacting you with a message that is very difficult for us personally. ZEGO Textilveredelungszentrum GmbH has filed for insolvency....<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F07%2F13%2Fa-cyberattack-in-march-resulted-in-zego-filing-for-insolvency%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Da-cyberattack-in-march-resulted-in-zego-filing-for-insolvency&amp;action_name=A%20cyberattack%20in%20March%20resulted%20in%20ZEGO%20filing%20for%20insolvency&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
