Fatima Abdullahi reports: The Federal High Court in Abuja has fixed July 21, 2026, for the arraignment of Zenith Bank Plc and three other defendants over allegations of illegally accessing and disclosing the confidential financial records of Makers Island Company Limited. The other defendants are Oluwaseyi Famousa, Paul Oku and Yesu-Felix Abosede Alice. Justice Hauwa...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F07%2F13%2Fng-zenith-bank-others-to-be-arraigned-over-alleged-data-breach%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dng-zenith-bank-others-to-be-arraigned-over-alleged-data-breach&amp;action_name=NG%3A%20Zenith%20Bank%2C%20Others%20To%20Be%20Arraigned%20Over%20Alleged%20Data%20Breach&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
